          "pk": 272,
          "book_id": "8A82C1696267E589CAC9B6E1E26D3AC1",
          "chapter": null,
          "text": " The gods might intrude, but he at least was resolved to follow a system that he had invented for the express purpose of following it.",
          "sentence": "He accepted that inevitable indeterminism which they now and then introduced, called it magic, and calmly proceeded to count the skins he had bartered by chalking bars on the wall of his cave. The gods might intrude, but he at least was resolved to follow a system that he had invented for the express purpose of following it.",
          "note": null,
          "path": "epubcfi(/6/48[Section0012.xhtml]!/4/28/1,:1513,:1647)",
          "created_at": "2021-07-15 23:04:27 -0700",
